wiki.summary: On “D.M.B.” (also stylized as DAT$ MAH B!*$H), A$AP Rocky utilizes chopped-and-screwed vocals to declare his love for drugs and women. The song was first previewed in an advertisement for Swedish fintech company Klarna on June 8, 2021. The song’s outro, which was featured in an extended cut of the Klarna commercial, was published as an audio on TikTok in early July 2021. On July 10, 2021, Rocky was spotted in New York City shooting a music video for the song with his girlfriend, Rihanna. Read more on Last.fm.
wiki.content: On “D.M.B.” (also stylized as DAT$ MAH B!*$H), A$AP Rocky utilizes chopped-and-screwed vocals to declare his love for drugs and women. The song was first previewed in an advertisement for Swedish fintech company Klarna on June 8, 2021. The song’s outro, which was featured in an extended cut of the Klarna commercial, was published as an audio on TikTok in early July 2021. On July 10, 2021, Rocky was spotted in New York City shooting a music video for the song with his girlfriend, Rihanna. Klarna confirmed in a comment on their Instagram post that this song is projected to be released “later this summer,” however, the song did not materialize by the end of summer 2021. Less than a year later, on May 3, 2022, Rocky previewed the single in a now deleted Instagram post, revealing the cover art of the single. The next day, Rocky shared a trailer for “D.M.B.” on all of his social media accounts. Read more on Last.fm.
